.SH NAME
evolve-models-discover - List vendor-served models and add new ones to the .evolve config


.SH SYNOPSIS
\fBevolve models discover [flags]\fP


.SH DESCRIPTION
Discover queries each vendor's model-listing API (using the same credentials
as token counting; vendors without a set key are skipped) and marks every model
already in the effective registry with where it lives (builtin or the config
file).

.PP
Interactively, the models render in a fuzzy-find picker: type to filter, tab to
select any number of new models, enter to write them into the repository's
\&.evolve config (created as .evolve.yaml when missing). Because a
providers.\&.models override replaces that provider's builtin list, the first
injected entry for a provider also seeds the list with its builtin models, so
the effective matrix only ever grows.

.PP
Vendor listing APIs publish no pricing, so injected entries carry none until
edited by hand; their costs render as unpublished in reports.


.SH OPTIONS
\fB-h\fP, \fB--help\fP[=false]
	help for discover

.PP
\fB--no-tui\fP[=false]
	print the discovered models instead of opening the interactive picker


.SH OPTIONS INHERITED FROM PARENT COMMANDS
\fB--json\fP[=false]
	emit machine-readable JSONL progress on stdout

.PP
\fB--layout\fP="auto"
	repository layout: auto, marketplace, multi, or single

.PP
\fB--results-format\fP=""
	format for results files and the EVALUATION rollup: json, jsonc, or yaml (default: config results_format or json)

.PP
\fB--root\fP=""
	repository root to operate on (default: walk up from the current directory)

.PP
\fB--telemetry-dir\fP=""
	write OpenTelemetry traces/metrics/logs as JSON to this directory (default: off; overrides OTEL_* env vars)

.PP
\fB-v\fP, \fB--verbose\fP[=false]
	enable debug logging


